09/09/2010
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Police arrested on Wednesday (September 8th) four former Croatian soldiers suspected of committing war crimes against Serbian prisoners of war and civilians during the 1991-1995 conflict.
The crimes allegedly occurred at the Kuline military prison in Sibenik in 1992.
The criminal proceedings were launched amid improved co-operation between Croatian and Serbian police services, local media reported.
(HRT, RTS, AP - 08/09/10)
